<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="access-n">access <strong><em>n</em></strong> ★</h1>
<p>英 /ˈækses/    美 /ˈækses/  </p>
<p>[U]</p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1">1.★ <strong>通道；入口</strong></h4>
<p>a way of reaching or entering a place：</p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>wheelchair access
轮椅通道；无障碍通道</p><footer>2020 全国</footer></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Fallen rocks cut off the only <strong>access to</strong> the village. 
坠石挡住了通往村子的唯一道路。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>The police <strong>gained access</strong> through a broken window.
警察从一扇破窗中钻了进去。</p></div>

<h4 id="2">2.★ <strong>使用 / 接近…的权利或机会</strong></h4>
<p>the opportunity or right to use sth or to see sb / sth：</p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Each room comes with its own bathroom and Internet access.
每个房间都有浴室，都能上网。</p><footer>译林① – 1</footer></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Across the world, 1.1 billion people <strong>have no access to</strong> clean drinking water.
全世界有11亿人喝不到干净的饮用水。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>This site gives you <strong>instant access to</strong> a wide range of information on studying and living in the UK.
这个网站让你瞬间即可查到关于在英国学习和居住的各种各样的信息。</p><footer>2008 广东</footer></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>One reason for her preference for city life is that she can <strong>have easy access to</strong> places like shops and restaurants. 
她喜欢城市生活的一个原因是去哪儿都很方便，比如去商店和餐馆。</p><footer>2010 上海</footer></div>

<p>注:   access ≠ way, access作为名词，其含义中包含了某种动作。   </p></div>